us Angels valuable to anyone interested in gender, culture, and narrative in nineteenth-century Europe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSex role in literature. 0aSpanish literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  a1892.  a19th century.  aangel of the house.  abenito prez galds.  abourgeois model.  aconduct literature.  aconservative.  aculture.  aemancipated new woman.  aeurope.  aevolution of feminism.  afeminism.  afrugal.  agender.  amedical texts.  amuted feminist discourse.  anarrative.  aperiodicals.  aspain.  astudying writing.  avirtuous womanhood.  awoman question.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008356140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520914179?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520914179423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520914179/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles